e herd if you have to.\0aThey might be planning a blood feast, but\0ayou feel about as mean as two thousand\0amaniacs packed into one mad killer.\0a\0aYou don't plan to go down easy.\00You've found the second-hardest level we\0agot. Hope you have a saved game a level or\0atwo previous.  If not, be prepared to die\0aaplenty. For master marines only.\00Picked up a yellow skull key.\00Picked up a blue skull key.\00Picked up a red skull key.\00this is the shareware version of doom.\0a\0ayou need to order the entire trilogy.\0a\0apress a key.\00you can't start a new game\0awhile in a network game.\0a\0apress a key.\00you haven't picked a quicksave slot yet!\0a\0apress a key.\00you can't save if you aren't playing!\0a\0apress a key.\00you can't quickload during a netgame!\0a\0apress a key.\00you can't end a netgame!\0a\0apress a key.\00you can't do load while in a net game!\0a\0apress a key.\00HU_Init: Setting up heads up display.\00Picked up a medikit.\00I'll take care of it.\00Picked up a rocket.\00just leave. when you come\0aback, i'll be waiting with a bat.\00D_CheckNetGame: Checking network game status.\00Picked up an armor bonus.\00Picked up a health bonus.\00M_LoadDefaults: Load system defaults.\00Picked up a box of bullets.\00Picked up a box of rockets.\00V_Init: allocate screens.\00get outta here and go back\0ato your boring programs.\00Picked up a box of shotgun shells.\00Picked up 4 shotgun shells.\00You got the BFG9000!  Oh, yes.\00The vista opening ahead looks real damn\0afamiliar. Smells familiar, too -- like\0afried excrement. You didn't like this\0aplace before, and you sure as hell ain't\0aplanning to like it now. The more you\0abrood on it, the madder you get.\0aHefting your gun, an evil grin trickles\0aonto your face. Time to take some names.\00W_Init: Init WADfiles.\00Picked up the armor.\00Suddenly, all is silent, from one horizon\0ato the other. The agonizing echo of Hell\0afades away, the nightmare sky turns to\0ablue, the heaps of monster corpses start \0ato evaporate along with the evil stench \0athat filled the air. Jeeze, maybe you've\0adone it. Have you really won?\0a\0aSomething rumbles in the distance.\0aA blue light begins to glow inside the\0aruined skull of the demon-spitter.\00ST_Init: Init status bar.\00Picked up a clip.\00You gloat over the steaming carcass of the\0aGuardian.  With its death, you've wrested\0athe Accelerator from the stinking claws\0aof Hell.  You relax and glance around the\0aroom.  Damn!  There was supposed to be at\0aleast one working prototype, but you can't\0asee it. The demons must have taken it.\0a\0aYou must find the prototype, or all your\0astruggles will have been wasted. Keep\0amoving, keep fighting, keep killing.\0aOh yes, keep living, too.\00You've done it! The hideous cyber-\0ademon lord that ruled the lost Deimos\0amoon base has been slain and you\0aare triumphant! But ... where are\0ayou? You clamber to the edge of the\0amoon and look down to see the awful\0atruth.\0a\0aDeimos floats above Hell itself!\0aYou've never heard of anyone escaping\0afrom Hell, but you'll make the bastards\0asorry they ever heard of you! Quickly,\0ayou rappel down to  the surface of\0aHell.\0a\0aNow, it's on to the final chapter of\0aDOOM! -- Inferno.\00M_Init: Init miscellaneous info.\00\0aThis is not the registered version.\00are you sure you want to end the game?\0a\0apress y or n.\00quicksave over your game named\0a\0a'%s'?\0a\0apress y or n.\00do you want to quickload the game named\0a\0a'%s'?\0a\0apress y or n.\00are you sure? this skill level\0aisn't even remotely fair.\0a\0apress y or n.\00Picked up an energy cell.\00THIS IS NO MESSAGE!\0aPage intentionally left blank.\00Picked up a stimpack.\00Picked up an energy cell pack.\00Even the deadly Arch-Vile labyrinth could\0anot stop you, and you've gotten to the\0aprototype Accelerator which is soon\0aefficiently and permanently deactivated.\0a\0aYou're good at that kind of thing.\00Betcha wondered just what WAS the hardest\0alevel we had ready for ya?  Now you know.\0aNo one gets out alive.\00\0aP_Init: Init Playloop state.\00I_Init: Setting up machine state.\00Game mode indeterminate.\00i wouldn't leave if i were you.\0ados is much worse.\00Time for a vacation. You've burst the\0abowels of hell and by golly you're ready\0afor a break. You mutter to yourself,\0aMaybe someone else can kick Hell's ass\0anext time around. Ahead lies a quiet town,\0awith peaceful flowing water, quaint\0abuildings, and presumably no Hellspawn.\0a\0aAs you step off the transport, you hear\0athe stomp of a cyberdemon's iron shoe.\00Picked up a yellow keycard.\00Picked up a blue keycard.\00Picked up a red keycard.\00S_Init: Setting up sound.\00You've fought your way out of the infested\0aexperimental labs.   It seems that UAC has\0aonce again gulped it down.  With their\0ahigh turnover, it must be hard for poor\0aold UAC to buy corporate health insurance\0anowadays..\0a\0aAhead lies the military complex, now\0aswarming with diseased horrors hot to get\0atheir teeth into you. With luck, the\0acomplex still has some warlike ordnance\0alaying around.\00game saved.\00Network game synchronization aborted.\00External statistics registered.\00i'd leave: this is just\0amore monsters and levels.\0awhat a load.\00ya know, next time you come in here\0ai'm gonna toast ya.\00YOU HAVE WON! YOUR VICTORY HAS ENABLED\0aHUMANKIND TO EVACUATE EARTH AND ESCAPE\0aTHE NIGHTMARE.  NOW YOU ARE THE ONLY\0aHUMAN LEFT ON THE FACE OF THE PLANET.\0aCANNIBAL MUTATIONS, CARNIVOROUS ALIENS,\0aAND EVIL SPIRITS ARE YOUR ONLY NEIGHBORS.\0aYOU SIT BACK AND WAIT FOR DEATH, CONTENT\0aTHAT YOU HAVE SAVED YOUR SPECIES.\0a\0aBUT THEN, EARTH CONTROL BEAMS DOWN A\0aMESSAGE FROM SPACE: \22SENSORS HAVE LOCATED\0aTHE SOURCE OF THE ALIEN INVASION. IF YOU\0aGO THERE, YOU MAY BE ABLE TO BLOCK THEIR\0aENTRY.  THE ALIEN BASE IS IN THE HEART OF\0aYOUR OWN HOME CITY, NOT FAR FROM THE\0aSTARPORT.\22 SLOWLY AND PAINFULLY YOU GET\0aUP AND RETURN TO THE FRAY.\00Development mode ON.\00I'm OK.\00YOU HAVE ENTERED DEEPLY INTO THE INFESTED\0aSTARPORT. BUT SOMETHING IS WRONG. THE\0aMONSTERS HAVE BROUGHT THEIR OWN REALITY\0aWITH THEM, AND THE STARPORT'S TECHNOLOGY\0aIS BEING SUBVERTED BY THEIR PRESENCE.\0a\0aAHEAD, YOU SEE AN OUTPOST OF HELL, A\0aFORTIFIED ZONE. IF YOU CAN GET PAST IT,\0aYOU CAN PENETRATE INTO THE HAUNTED HEART\0aOF THE STARBASE AND FIND THE CONTROLLING\0aSWITCH WHICH HOLDS EARTH'S POPULATION\0aHOSTAGE.\00CONGRATULATIONS, YOU'VE FOUND THE SECRET\0aLEVEL! LOOKS LIKE IT'S BEEN BUILT BY\0aHUMANS, RATHER THAN DEMONS. YOU WONDER\0aWHO THE INMATES OF THIS CORNER OF HELL\0aWILL BE.\00What now? Looks totally different. Kind\0aof like King Tut's condo. Well,\0awhatever's here can't be any worse\0athan usual. Can it?  Or maybe it's best\0ato let sleeping gods lie..\00You've lost it...\00listening for network start info...\00sending network start info...\00Changing Level...\00Next time, scumbag...\00The loathsome spiderdemon that\0amasterminded the invasion of the moon\0abases and caused so much death has had\0aits ass kicked for all time.\0a\0aA hidden doorway opens and you enter.\0aYou've proven too tough for Hell to\0acontain, and now Hell at last plays\0afair -- for you emerge from the door\0ato see the green fields of Earth!\0aHome at last.\0a\0aYou wonder what's been happening on\0aEarth while you were battling evil\0aunleashed. It's good that no Hell-\0aspawn could have come through that\0adoor with you ...\00The Gatekeeper's evil face is splattered\0aall over the place.  As its tattered corpse\0acollapses, an inverted Gate forms and\0asucks down the shards of the last\0aprototype Accelerator, not to mention the\0afew remaining demons.  You're done. Hell\0ahas gone back to pounding bad dead folks \0ainstead of good live ones.  Remember to\0atell your grandkids to put a rocket\0alauncher in your coffin. If you go to Hell\0awhen you die, you'll need it for some\0afinal cleaning-up ...\00ang=0x%x;x,y=(0x%x,0x%x)\00%s\0a\0a(press y t